# Simulation of Intelligent Robot Navigation using IR-SIM

## üìå Project Overview
This project demonstrates intelligent robot navigation in a simulated environment using **IR-SIM (Intelligent Robot Simulator)** integrated with the **RDA (Regularized Dual ADMM) Motion Planner**.  
The simulation focuses on autonomous navigation, collision avoidance, sensor-based perception, and trajectory tracking without the need for physical robot hardware.

The project was developed as part of the **Computer Organization and Architecture (COA)** coursework and draws parallels between robotic control flow and the CPU **fetch‚Äìdecode‚Äìexecute** cycle.

---

## üéØ Objectives
- Understand the working of a lightweight Python-based robot simulation framework  
- Simulate intelligent navigation for different robot models  
- Implement collision detection and dynamic obstacle avoidance  
- Visualize robot trajectory, environment, and sensor data  
- Relate robotic control flow to core COA concepts  

---

## üß† Technologies Used
- **Programming Language:** Python 3.9+  
- **Simulation Framework:** IR-SIM  
- **Motion Planning:** RDA (Regularized Dual ADMM Planner)  
- **Libraries:** NumPy, Matplotlib, PyYAML  
- **Configuration:** YAML-based environment definition  

